### Summary
- Stream 5 deliverables (state container, autosave hook, draft server actions, resume dialog) were already present in `lib/forms/form-state.ts`, `hooks/use-autosave.ts`, `app/forms/actions.ts`, and related components, so the main gap was wiring Streams 6–7 into the wizard experience.
- `DynamicFormWizard` now builds a field-visibility map, hides conditional fields, filters error summaries, and only validates steps with currently visible inputs, so conditional logic from Stream 6 finally drives both UX and validation.^
```49:132:components/forms/dynamic-form-wizard.tsx
const allFields = useMemo(
  () => sortedSections.flatMap((section) => section.fields),
  [sortedSections]
);

...

const visibilityMap = useFieldVisibility(allFields, state.formData);

...

const focusFirstError = useCallback(
  (fieldKey?: string) => {
    if (!fieldKey || !currentSection) {
      return;
    }

    const isVisible = visibilityMap[fieldKey] ?? true;
    if (!isVisible) {
      return;
    }

    const errorField = currentSection.fields.find((field) => field.key === fieldKey);
    const fieldElement = errorField
      ? document.getElementById(`field-${errorField.id}`)
      : null;
    fieldElement?.focus();
    fieldElement?.scrollIntoView({ behavior: "smooth", block: "center" });
  },
  [currentSection, visibilityMap]
);
```
- `useFormState` exposes `validateStepAt/validateAndCommitStep` overloads that accept `ValidateStepOptions`, ensuring touched/error tracking ignores hidden inputs and stays in sync with the wizard’s visibility map.^
```269:289:hooks/use-form-state.ts
const validateStepAt = useCallback(
  (stepIndex: number, options?: ValidateStepOptions) => {
    const result = validateStep(stepIndex, state.formData, formConfig, options);
    const fieldKeys = getStepFieldKeys(stepIndex, formConfig).filter(
      (fieldKey) => options?.visibilityMap?.[fieldKey] ?? true
    );
    return {
      ...result,
      fieldKeys,
    };
  },
  [formConfig, state.formData]
);

const validateAndCommitStep = useCallback(
  (stepIndex: number, options?: ValidateStepOptions) => {
    const validation = validateStepAt(stepIndex, options);
    markFieldsTouched(validation.fieldKeys);
    setStepErrors(validation.fieldKeys, validation.errors);
    return validation;
  },
  [markFieldsTouched, setStepErrors, validateStepAt]
);
```
- Autosave feedback from Stream 7 now matches the UX spec: `DraftSaveIndicator` shares the same status enum as `useAutosave`, gracefully handles string/Date timestamps, and renders human-friendly relative times instead of stale “not saved” text.^
```1:51:components/forms/draft-save-indicator.tsx
import { formatDistanceToNow } from "date-fns";
import type { AutosaveStatus } from "@/hooks/use-autosave";

export type DraftStatus = AutosaveStatus;

...

export function DraftSaveIndicator({
  status,
  lastSavedAt,
  errorMessage,
  className,
}: DraftSaveIndicatorProps) {
  const readableTimestamp = getReadableTimestamp(lastSavedAt);
  let icon = <Save className="size-4" aria-hidden="true" />;
  let message = readableTimestamp ? `Draft saved ${readableTimestamp}` : "Draft not saved yet";

  if (status === "saving") {
    icon = <Loader2 className="size-4 animate-spin" aria-hidden="true" />;
    message = "Saving draft…";
  } else if (status === "saved" && readableTimestamp) {
    icon = <CheckCircle2 className="size-4 text-emerald-600" aria-hidden="true" />;
    message = `Draft saved ${readableTimestamp}`;
  } else if (status === "error") {
    icon = <AlertTriangle className="size-4 text-destructive" aria-hidden="true" />;
    message = errorMessage ?? "Unable to save draft. Please try again.";
  }

  ...
}
```

## Summary
- Resolved the Next.js dynamic-route slug collision by moving the form routes into route groups (`app/forms/(by-entity)/[formSlug]/[geographyCode]`, `app/forms/(by-config)/[formSlug]`) and updating each page to pull `formSlug` from `params`. This keeps the public URLs stable while satisfying the framework’s slug-name rule.
- Added a dev-only preview route (`app/dev/wizard-preview/page.tsx`) that renders `DynamicFormWizard` with a mocked `FormConfigWithFields`. This bypasses auth/DB requirements so we can exercise responsive behavior and a11y semantics locally (page throws `notFound()` in production builds).
- Verified that conditional visibility wiring works end-to-end in the preview (e.g., `swift_code` only appears when “Net 60” is selected) and captured evidence showing both visible/hidden states.

## Testing
- `npm run test`
- Manual responsive & SR spot checks on `http://localhost:8000/dev/wizard-preview`:
  - Desktop layout & semantics (`.playwright-mcp/page-2025-11-18T09-02-23-300Z.png`)
  - Tablet breakpoint (`.playwright-mcp/tablet-preview.png`)
  - Mobile breakpoint w/ sticky nav + stacked fields (`.playwright-mcp/mobile-preview.png`)
  - Step 2 with SWIFT field visible when `preferred_terms = Net 60` (`.playwright-mcp/step-2-conditional.png`)
  - Step 2 with SWIFT hidden when `preferred_terms = Net 30` (`.playwright-mcp/step-2-no-swift.png`)
  - Spot-checked SR affordances via the browser’s accessibility tree: step indicator rendered as `nav[aria-label="Form progress"]`, draft state + current-step announcements surfaced through `role="status"` regions, and each control exposes labels/`aria-describedby` text.

## Notes / Follow-ups
- Because preview traffic isn’t authenticated, autosave calls intentionally fail with “Unauthorized”; the toast (and `DraftSaveIndicator`) still present accessible error messaging, but keep in mind this noise won’t happen in real flows with a valid session.
- Dev preview is guarded by `process.env.NODE_ENV !== "production"` via `notFound()`, so it won’t leak into prod builds.
